OL,7,F"I've got like little voice in my head
OL,8,Ffrom her basically saying, 'Get out,
OL,9,Fmum and get carrying on.' All this is
OL,10,Fwhat she will be proud of and what a
OL,11,Fbetter way to make a legacy for her."
OL,13,FThe Daily Mirror Pride of Britain
OL,14,FAwards celebrate the unsung heroes who
OL,15,Fgo above and beyond to make their
OL,16,Fcommunities and the country a better
OL,17,Fplace.
OL,19,FNominated by the public, the winners
OL,20,Fcome from all walks of life, of all
OL,21,Fages, and from all over the country.
